Model Artifacts Summary

This project includes several trained machine learning models and preprocessing components used in the final ensemble system:

• XGBoost Model (xgb_model_v3.pkl)
  - Primary gradient boosting model
  - Provides strong baseline performance and supports SHAP-based interpretability

• LightGBM Model (lgb_model_v3.pkl)
  - High-efficiency boosting model
  - Contributes to improved generalization in the ensemble

• Random Forest Model (rf_model_v3.pkl)
  - Reduces variance and improves robustness
  - Helps stabilize predictions across different time periods

• Ensemble Weights (ensemble_weights.pkl)
  - Defines weighted combination:
    XGBoost (25%), LightGBM (45%), Random Forest (30%)

• Feature Pipeline
  - feature_cols_v*.pkl: list of selected features
  - scaler objects: normalize and standardize inputs

• Deep Learning Components (GAT-Transformer)
  - gat_features.pkl: graph node features
  - gat_graph_data.pkl: spatial graph structure
  - gat_feat_scaler.pkl / gat_target_scaler.pkl: scaling
  - transformer model files: temporal sequence modeling

Note:
Due to GitHub file size limitations, model artifacts are not uploaded.
The repository includes code to retrain models or load them locally.
